cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.DS 

The paper deals with models in concurrency theory, specifically event structures, trace automata, and Petri nets. It also discusses graph theoretical and geometric interpretations of these structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also uses geometric group theory, which suggests a possible fit in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
